WEBVTT

00:01.169 --> 00:03.045
NARRATOR:
Previously on Prison Break .'

00:03.212 --> 00:06.465
Listen, why don't I give you
half the money and we call it a day?

00:06.632 --> 00:08.092
All right, 60-40.

00:08.259 --> 00:10.094
You thieving son of a bitch.

00:10.261 --> 00:13.472
You better get down on your knees
and pray to God that I don't find you.

00:13.639 --> 00:17.727
Because if I do, mark my words,
I'm gonna gut you bow to stern.

00:17.894 --> 00:19.478
SLATTERY: Mr. Bellick?
- Yeah.

00:19.645 --> 00:21.647
SLATTERY: Do you mind answering
a few more questions?

00:21.814 --> 00:24.567
KIM: We have a lead as to where
Burrows will meet with his brother.

00:24.734 --> 00:26.527
A place he referred to
as Bolshoi Booze.

00:26.694 --> 00:27.862
MAHONE:
They're numbers.

00:28.029 --> 00:29.405
WHEELER:
Plug them into your GPS.

00:29.572 --> 00:32.325
It'll take you to a spot
in the New Mexico desert.

00:32.616 --> 00:34.869
H -Daddy!
_ ey' baby- You ready to 90v

00:36.037 --> 00:37.705
Come on. Go, go, go!

00:38.831 --> 00:40.333
What do we do now?

00:44.337 --> 00:46.214
KIM: <i>Has she fold you anything?
- Not yet.</i>

00:46.380 --> 00:48.883
- Then kill her.
- Well, if she knows something...

00:49.050 --> 00:50.551
You disobey me, you are done.

00:50.718 --> 00:52.053
<i>Put her in the ground, Paul.</i>

00:52.220 --> 00:53.429
You're going to die.

00:53.596 --> 00:56.724
And all you had to do was tell me
what your father gave you.

00:56.891 --> 00:58.184
Go to hell.

01:03.648 --> 01:06.484
The plane's gonna stop
at the seven-mile marker...

01:06.651 --> 01:08.736
...Route Four, at sunset.

01:08.903 --> 01:11.197
- We gotta go.
- I brought someone. Dad?

01:13.699 --> 01:14.909
We've met before.

01:19.622 --> 01:21.916
- It was you.
- Go easy, son.

01:23.459 --> 01:24.752
Stay away from me.

01:26.087 --> 01:27.880
- What the hell's going on?
- I know him.

01:28.047 --> 01:31.425
- You know him? That's impossible.
- I know him. I know this man.

01:40.810 --> 01:42.353
- Michael.
- Maybe that's far enough.

01:42.520 --> 01:45.356
- This doesn't concern you.
- What the hell's going on, Dad?

01:49.068 --> 01:50.528
[SIGHS]

01:51.612 --> 01:53.114
After Mom died...

01:54.407 --> 01:56.617
...you were in juvie.

01:57.827 --> 02:01.789
They put me with this foster father...

02:01.956 --> 02:04.542
...down on Pershing Avenue.

02:06.627 --> 02:08.713
He punished me.

02:09.463 --> 02:11.299
Locked me up.

02:11.966 --> 02:14.635
<i>If you leave someone alone
in the dark for that long...</i>

02:16.512 --> 02:17.972
<i>...their eyes start to adjust.</i>

02:19.140 --> 02:23.477
<i>You start to see things,
no matter how small...</i>

02:24.145 --> 02:28.482
<i>...because if they exist,
they can help you.</i>

02:31.736 --> 02:33.654
<i>Help you do
the only thing you wanna do...</i>

02:33.821 --> 02:35.406
<i>...when you're alone in the dark.</i>

02:38.117 --> 02:39.744
<i>Get out.</i>

03:09.148 --> 03:11.692
<i>MAN [ON</i> TV]: <i>I've used just about
every lure that you can use.</i>

03:12.401 --> 03:14.862
<i>Most of them,
you need to be an expert to use.</i>

03:15.029 --> 03:16.864
<i>This MotoLure's a little different.</i>

03:17.031 --> 03:18.949
<i>Everybody, I mean,
everybody, can fish with it.</i>

03:19.158 --> 03:20.242
[KNOCKING]

03:20.451 --> 03:23.245
<i>Catch bigger fish,
you're gonna catch more fish.</i>

03:23.412 --> 03:27.875
<i>It even works in weedy areas
where most top water lures won't work.</i>

03:28.042 --> 03:30.753
<i>Take a look at this baby.
This thing looks like a real minnow.</i>

03:30.920 --> 03:32.004
[KNOCKING]

03:32.171 --> 03:33.381
<i>It's one very cool bait.</i>

03:33.798 --> 03:36.717
<i>I have never seen
anything quite like this.</i>

03:36.884 --> 03:40.179
<i>Even if you've bought lures off TV
in the past and been disappointed...</i>

03:40.346 --> 03:42.223
<i>...and believe me, I know how you feel.</i>

03:42.390 --> 03:46.519
- Oh, sorry, man. I thought you'd left.
- Hey. No, still here. Here I am.

03:46.685 --> 03:48.854
It's just that a couple guests
are complaining...

03:49.021 --> 03:50.481
...about the volume of your TV.

03:50.648 --> 03:55.069
Oh, sorry. I fell asleep.
I must've hit the remote.

03:55.236 --> 03:57.905
<i>- I'll</i> take care of it. Thanks. Sorry. Thanks.
- That's great.

03:59.198 --> 04:02.660
So could you do that for me now,
please, so it's taken care of?

04:02.827 --> 04:05.371
- Yeah.
- Thanks.

04:15.506 --> 04:17.341
Taken care of.

04:17.716 --> 04:19.468
[WATER SPLASHING]

04:19.677 --> 04:21.720
Is everything okay in your bathroom?

04:23.139 --> 04:24.974
Excuse me?

04:25.224 --> 04:27.560
MANAGER: In your bathroom.
There's a noise coming from it.

04:27.726 --> 04:30.604
KELLERMAN: Yeah, my daughter
thinks bath time is playtime.

04:31.021 --> 04:33.941
I will clean it up. Scout's honor. Sorry.

04:35.234 --> 04:37.403
- All right. Have a nice day.
- Yeah.

04:37.570 --> 04:39.655
You too.

04:50.291 --> 04:51.500
ALDO: Michael!
LINCOLN: Michael.

04:51.667 --> 04:54.128
- Michael, please, wait.
- He did this to you?

04:54.295 --> 04:55.421
Lincoln!

04:57.923 --> 04:59.967
He did this to you?

05:01.886 --> 05:03.471
Did he do this to you?

05:09.727 --> 05:11.479
Michael.

05:12.396 --> 05:15.316
How could you do that
to another human being...

05:15.483 --> 05:17.651
...with your own hands?

05:27.912 --> 05:29.497
It's okay.

05:29.663 --> 05:31.582
You're safe now.

05:35.836 --> 05:38.506
He's not gonna hurt you anymore.

05:46.555 --> 05:48.349
Come on.

05:49.558 --> 05:52.102
Come with me and don't look back.

06:03.405 --> 06:05.324
Michael!

06:06.700 --> 06:08.661
Michael.

06:16.085 --> 06:17.336
It's gonna be all right.

06:23.175 --> 06:25.886
[WATER DRAINING]

06:32.601 --> 06:34.687
[KELLERMAN SCREAMING]

07:02.047 --> 07:04.133
[CAR ALARM WAILING]

07:06.176 --> 07:07.428
[GRUNTING]

07:11.473 --> 07:12.516
KELLERMAN:
Sara!

09:12.511 --> 09:13.887
<i>MICHAEL:
Six months.</i>

09:14.555 --> 09:17.307
Six months I was in that place.

09:17.766 --> 09:19.601
Where were you?

09:20.227 --> 09:21.437
How long did you know?

09:21.603 --> 09:24.189
I found you as soon as I could.
The state kept moving you.

09:24.356 --> 09:25.607
Then you went away again.

09:25.774 --> 09:28.152
You don't think it killed me
to leave you like that?

09:28.318 --> 09:29.820
To leave in the first place?

09:29.987 --> 09:31.739
Since the beginning, I was the problem.

09:31.905 --> 09:34.867
Since day one. Your lives
are what they are because of me.

09:35.033 --> 09:36.744
Yes, Linc told me about The Company.

09:36.910 --> 09:40.539
You were some kind of analyst. That's
the job you chose over your family.

09:40.664 --> 09:43.083
I thought I was doing the right thing,
protecting you.

09:43.250 --> 09:44.918
From what, Dad? From who?

09:45.669 --> 09:48.881
The Company had enemies.
I was important to The Company.

09:49.047 --> 09:52.426
I became a target. Easiest way
to get to me would be to get to you.

09:53.093 --> 09:55.220
I left as soon as I realized
how corrupt it was.

09:55.387 --> 09:58.182
- How they were buying the government.
- You could've come back.

09:58.348 --> 09:59.933
No, I couldn't!

10:00.100 --> 10:04.772
Michael, turning on The Company
put me and you at even greater risk.

10:05.355 --> 10:07.608
I had to stay away.

10:08.400 --> 10:10.194
We were your sons.

10:10.360 --> 10:11.904
And you still are, Michael.

10:12.654 --> 10:14.615
We can fix this.

10:14.782 --> 10:17.701
I came back so that we could fix this.

10:19.453 --> 10:21.789
This can never be fixed.

10:25.000 --> 10:26.835
There's a tape.

10:27.795 --> 10:29.922
It gives us everything we need.

10:31.089 --> 10:33.884
Linc will be set free if we find it.

10:34.051 --> 10:36.470
You're not gonna believe
who he thinks has it.

10:37.304 --> 10:38.806
Who?

10:39.431 --> 10:40.974
Sara.

10:45.062 --> 10:49.024
Yes, tall, slender,
brown hair, brown eyes.

10:49.191 --> 10:51.068
She'd be pretty banged up.

10:51.235 --> 10:53.445
WOMAN <i>[OVER</i> PHONE]: <i>No one matching that description. - .</i>

10:53.612 --> 10:55.113
<i>...has been brought into the ER.</i>

10:59.409 --> 11:00.911
Kellerman.

11:01.078 --> 11:02.538
The report on Sara Tancredi?

11:02.704 --> 11:04.998
She's dead.
I'm dealing with the body right now.

11:07.167 --> 11:09.461
- You must be relieved that it's over.
<i>- Yeah.</i>

11:09.628 --> 11:12.256
- Yeah, I gotta go, Bill.
- One more <i>thing.</i>

11:12.464 --> 11:13.674
<i>Confirmation.</i>

11:14.174 --> 11:16.468
I need a photo of the body
before disposal.

11:16.635 --> 11:19.012
<i>Take one with your phone
and send it to me, and I'll--</i>

11:19.179 --> 11:21.682
Bill, not a good time right now,
all right?

11:23.141 --> 11:26.061
Paul, take a breath...

11:26.478 --> 11:28.647
...then take the picture.

11:28.856 --> 11:30.482
I'm waiting.

11:32.067 --> 11:33.402
[PHONE HANGS UP]

11:39.908 --> 11:43.537
FRANKLIN: "They traveled
into a very dangerous place.

11:43.704 --> 11:47.207
Now, Arvid knew that, but he held
tightly onto the dragon's leash anyway...

11:47.374 --> 11:49.710
...as the creature ran
into the ever-dark forest...

11:49.877 --> 11:52.045
...pulling the young boy behind him."

11:52.588 --> 11:54.923
Why didn't he just let go of the leash?

11:55.090 --> 11:58.051
Well, because he loved the dragon.

11:58.218 --> 12:02.890
And when you love someone,
you'll do anything to hold onto them.

12:03.223 --> 12:06.476
Anything to keep them safe and happy.

12:06.894 --> 12:08.520
Is that why we're camping?

12:09.688 --> 12:12.024
Yep, so we can all be together.

12:13.066 --> 12:14.735
<i>I'm â€œEDDY-</i>

12:17.487 --> 12:19.740
You know, I'm happy too.

12:26.830 --> 12:28.707
Here you go.

12:41.970 --> 12:43.430
Well, it's all working out, huh?

12:44.222 --> 12:46.183
Don't say that.

12:59.780 --> 13:02.991
You know, this moment,
right here, right now...

13:03.992 --> 13:06.244
...it's all worth it.

13:09.748 --> 13:11.792
I love you.

13:12.334 --> 13:13.585
I love you.

13:39.945 --> 13:41.154
Oh, that's old.

13:41.655 --> 13:44.491
- The kids are bigger now.
- Sorry, I was just...

13:44.658 --> 13:48.078
Oh, getting bored out of your wits
because you've been waiting so long.

13:48.245 --> 13:50.080
I'm really sorry about all this.

13:50.247 --> 13:52.499
We don't get a whole bunch
of homicides out here...

13:52.666 --> 13:55.335
...and we're trying to play catch-up.
Please, have a seat.

13:58.380 --> 14:00.507
I'm real sorry about your friend.

14:01.383 --> 14:03.802
It's a sick world out there.

14:03.927 --> 14:06.013
Ain't that the truth.

14:06.596 --> 14:09.850
- So you guys out here in Kansas together?
- Yeah, that's right.

14:10.267 --> 14:11.518
Doing what?

14:11.977 --> 14:13.729
Well, you know, just seeing the sights.

14:13.895 --> 14:16.565
You left Chicago to see the sights
in Tribune, Kansas?

14:16.732 --> 14:18.817
Last I checked,
a man could go where he wanted.

14:18.942 --> 14:21.737
- Mr. Bellick.
- Brad.

14:22.904 --> 14:24.406
Brad.

14:24.573 --> 14:26.992
I don't really care
what you were doing out here.

14:27.159 --> 14:31.204
We're both in law enforcement. We
can each sniff out a perp like a hot fart.

14:31.747 --> 14:33.957
Pardon my French.

14:34.416 --> 14:36.710
And we both know
you're not a criminal...

14:37.252 --> 14:41.882
...so I don't care if you boys were out
here whooping it without your wives...

14:43.133 --> 14:44.384
...or going Brokeback.

14:44.551 --> 14:46.053
What?

14:46.219 --> 14:47.429
Hell, no.

14:47.596 --> 14:50.182
My point is,
I don't care what you were doing.

14:50.348 --> 14:54.227
I just need to know where you were doing
it and who you crossed paths with...

14:54.394 --> 14:56.938
...so I can find out
who carved up Mr. Geary.

15:01.943 --> 15:07.991
Geary and I got a lead that one
of the Fox River Eight was in town.

15:08.867 --> 15:09.868
Which one?

15:10.494 --> 15:13.413
- Theodore Bagwell.
- The man who did those horrible things...

15:13.580 --> 15:15.457
-...to those teenagers?
- That's him.

15:15.624 --> 15:19.002
We were gonna bring him in for the
reward, but we couldn't get a handle.

15:19.169 --> 15:21.880
Geary and I split up,
we figured we didn't have a shot, but--

15:22.047 --> 15:24.049
- But what?
- Well, after what happened...

15:24.216 --> 15:28.136
...I'm starting to think maybe Geary
ran into old Bagwell after all.

15:28.553 --> 15:30.972
Right here in Tribune?

15:32.516 --> 15:35.227
Now, Brad, do you think
you could answer some questions...

15:35.393 --> 15:38.605
...that might help us, you know,
track down Theodore Bagwell?

15:38.772 --> 15:40.273
I'd be indebted.

15:40.440 --> 15:43.819
I'll do whatever I can to help nail
that son of a bitch.

15:43.985 --> 15:45.904
You think Sara has this tape?

15:46.029 --> 15:47.405
The government does.

15:49.449 --> 15:51.827
I just saw her yesterday.
If she does have anything...

15:51.993 --> 15:53.286
...she doesn't know.

15:53.912 --> 15:56.748
- Well, where is she now?
- I don't know.

15:57.249 --> 15:59.584
Any way you can
get in touch with her?

15:59.751 --> 16:02.963
- We bought cell phones. I could call her.
- Please, please, please, bro.

16:03.130 --> 16:05.715
Call her from Panama, please.

16:05.924 --> 16:08.260
We got less than two hours.
I gotta make the flight.

16:08.426 --> 16:10.470
[ROCKS CLATTERING]

16:11.054 --> 16:12.681
Shh, shh, Shh.

16:12.848 --> 16:14.182
What?

16:18.520 --> 16:20.605
Run. Run!

16:27.154 --> 16:30.115
- Where's this car you keep talking about?
- It's over the ridge.

16:30.282 --> 16:32.284
Give me that.
You guys head for the car.

16:33.201 --> 16:34.953
Go!

16:42.544 --> 16:43.628
LINCOLN:
Come on, come on!

16:51.344 --> 16:53.180
Come on! Go, go, go!

16:54.723 --> 16:56.057
Pick up Dad!

16:58.310 --> 17:00.145
Dad, get in!

17:03.356 --> 17:05.233
Come on, Dad!

17:13.366 --> 17:17.412
SUCRE: Woo-hoo-hoo! We made it!
Son of a bitch, we made it!

17:24.211 --> 17:25.753
Linc.

17:39.434 --> 17:41.686
Sucre, get us to a hospital.

17:41.853 --> 17:46.274
- Out here? Where am I gonna find--?
- Just get us to a hospital, please!

17:46.441 --> 17:48.944
Don't worry, you're gonna make it.

17:49.152 --> 17:52.155
It's bile. He got me clean through.

17:52.322 --> 17:55.450
You're gonna be okay. Just hold on.

17:55.617 --> 17:58.036
Listen to me, both of you.

18:00.288 --> 18:02.123
Sorry.

18:02.290 --> 18:04.584
I wish I'd never left.

18:04.793 --> 18:06.211
[ALDO COUGHING]

18:06.378 --> 18:09.839
Don't talk. Just breathe, okay?

18:14.386 --> 18:17.264
Okay. So do you want a P.B.& B.?

18:17.430 --> 18:21.142
Not really. My tummy hurts.

18:21.309 --> 18:22.769
FRANKLIN:
Huh.

18:23.103 --> 18:24.312
Where's her knapsack?

18:25.438 --> 18:26.481
Her what?

18:27.274 --> 18:31.152
- Her knapsack. Her medicine's in it.
- I don't know. I just grabbed her and ran.

18:31.319 --> 18:34.155
She needs that medicine.
She can't go two days without it.

18:34.864 --> 18:36.825
Okay, I know. I'm her father, all right?

18:37.993 --> 18:39.327
Where is it?

18:39.494 --> 18:42.163
Baby, baby. Look, look, calm down.
What are you looking for?

18:42.330 --> 18:45.083
Just tell me what it is
and I'll go ahead and get it, okay?

18:45.250 --> 18:46.960
Her prescription.

18:48.378 --> 18:51.172
It's a backup. I keep an extra, in case.

18:51.339 --> 18:53.591
Okay, okay.

18:53.758 --> 18:58.930
So all I need to do is find a pharmacy.

19:02.809 --> 19:04.769
Don't worry.

19:04.978 --> 19:07.981
Hey, looks like we're going on a ride,
sweet pea.

19:08.148 --> 19:11.484
If we nail Bagwell, he might still have
some of Geary's things on him...

19:11.651 --> 19:14.195
...like his backpack,
which has his personal stuff in it.

19:14.362 --> 19:16.781
I know his wife would love to have it.

19:16.948 --> 19:17.991
If we find Bagwell...

19:18.158 --> 19:19.868
-...give it to her personally.
- Thanks.

19:20.035 --> 19:23.163
It's the least I can do
considering how you're helping me out.

19:23.330 --> 19:26.249
Although some of the guys
on the force are concerned about...

19:26.416 --> 19:30.003
- What are they concerned about?
- Oh, nothing.

19:30.587 --> 19:32.881
You know what?
Why don't you tell me what you know?

19:33.048 --> 19:35.800
We'll track down Bagwell,
get Geary's effects to his family.

19:35.967 --> 19:38.887
I'll make sure everybody involved knows
your help was invaluable.

19:39.054 --> 19:42.974
I'll even recommend that you get most of,
if not all of that reward money.

19:43.641 --> 19:47.729
Well, what is it exactly that the guys
on the force were concerned about?

19:49.939 --> 19:53.318
Some of them thought you weren't
being totally upfront about your injury.

19:53.485 --> 19:56.863
I mean, to be fair, it does seem
a little off that you didn't see the guy...

19:57.030 --> 20:00.408
...who hit you smack-dab
on the forehead.

20:03.995 --> 20:05.705
You got me.

20:06.956 --> 20:11.252
Geary and me had a little dust-up
over how to go about finding Bagwell.

20:11.419 --> 20:14.756
It got physical and he hit me.

20:14.923 --> 20:18.760
The two of us, we fought like brothers.
I didn't wanna rat him out to the cops.

20:20.261 --> 20:23.264
After the fight, we split up.

20:23.932 --> 20:25.433
And then...

20:27.977 --> 20:29.687
Well, you know what happened to him.

20:29.896 --> 20:31.606
[CRYING]

20:31.773 --> 20:33.983
I just wish to hell we'd never fought,
you know.

20:34.192 --> 20:36.903
Maybe then, he'd still be...

20:38.279 --> 20:40.740
Brad, you can't blame yourself.

20:43.660 --> 20:48.039
Why don't we refocus our energy on
finding the man who killed your friend?

20:51.000 --> 20:53.628
That's what Roy would've wanted.

21:12.480 --> 21:14.149
Where you at, baby?

21:16.025 --> 21:18.069
Insurance card?

21:18.236 --> 21:20.405
No, I don't have insurance.

21:20.572 --> 21:23.491
You're paying for dexamethasone
without insurance?

21:23.658 --> 21:26.828
You got Medicaid,
Medicare or something?

21:27.162 --> 21:29.247
Nope. I'll just pay cash.

21:29.956 --> 21:31.749
It's 125.

21:43.261 --> 21:45.263
KACEE:
Excuse me.

21:46.181 --> 21:48.057
Excuse me?

21:49.767 --> 21:51.144
Oh, sorry.

22:01.362 --> 22:04.324
I'm sorry I don't have
anything smaller.

22:04.741 --> 22:05.950
Um...

22:06.117 --> 22:08.453
I have to go to the back
to get change for a hundred.

22:08.620 --> 22:10.288
So I'll be right back.

22:23.134 --> 22:25.094
- Right there, hospital!
- I see it, I see it.

22:25.303 --> 22:27.305
MICHAEL: Just get us there.
- No, you'll be caught.

22:27.430 --> 22:29.307
Then we'll be caught.

22:30.058 --> 22:31.559
I'm not gonna let you die.

22:32.018 --> 22:33.811
ALDO:
Then listen to me.

22:33.978 --> 22:36.898
You find Sara Tancredi.

22:37.315 --> 22:39.442
She can end this.

22:40.818 --> 22:43.029
It's up to you now.

22:48.201 --> 22:49.536
[COUGHS]

22:54.165 --> 22:58.628
Yeah, I want an alarm out
on a dark blue sedan, license AE 9268.

22:58.795 --> 23:01.214
Forty miles southeast of Las Cruces.

23:01.756 --> 23:04.008
Do it now.

23:04.884 --> 23:06.052
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

23:06.219 --> 23:08.263
Oh, come on.

23:09.806 --> 23:11.474
What?

23:13.101 --> 23:14.519
What hospital?

23:21.943 --> 23:24.904
Came in with a bad GSW.
Docs called us in.

23:25.071 --> 23:27.115
He's in here.

23:27.282 --> 23:28.825
We ran his name.

23:28.992 --> 23:32.829
Came back with two federal
drug-smuggling warrants out on him.

23:33.913 --> 23:35.373
Heard you wanted to talk to me.

23:39.419 --> 23:41.796
I got some information the feds want.

23:43.131 --> 23:45.133
About Michael Scofield.

23:48.970 --> 23:51.097
Like where he's catching a ride.

23:51.973 --> 23:54.225
And where would that be?

23:54.934 --> 23:59.230
It's not just the where, but the when.

24:00.148 --> 24:02.317
That when is coming up soon.

24:03.985 --> 24:05.987
But I wanna cut a deal first.

24:09.240 --> 24:11.159
Give us a minute?

24:21.753 --> 24:23.421
LINCOLN:
Anything you wanna say?

24:25.465 --> 24:27.175
One day.

24:28.426 --> 24:30.511
That's all we had.

24:54.494 --> 24:59.374
Back then,
when things were at their worst...

25:00.375 --> 25:03.711
...there were days I thought
I'd never see the sun again.

25:04.671 --> 25:06.839
But he saved my life.

25:11.010 --> 25:14.180
Just wish he could've let us
be a part of his.

25:19.852 --> 25:21.521
Yeah.

25:30.405 --> 25:32.240
I'll tell him.

25:37.036 --> 25:38.621
Here's the deal.

25:38.788 --> 25:41.374
All charges dropped,
government picks up medical costs...

25:41.541 --> 25:43.167
...until you're fit to be deported.

25:43.334 --> 25:46.879
All contingent upon your information
being accurate.

25:48.423 --> 25:49.674
Where's Scofield?

25:50.758 --> 25:53.928
No deportation. I want citizenship.

25:55.263 --> 25:57.306
Citizenship?

25:57.515 --> 26:01.352
A little incentive,
and I want it in writing.

26:01.519 --> 26:03.730
Oh, I'm so tired of playing games.

26:04.313 --> 26:06.190
Well, start typing.

26:11.988 --> 26:13.030
[BEEPING]

26:13.197 --> 26:14.449
No external pacemaker.

26:15.867 --> 26:19.579
Hey, this is a good one.
No morphine drip.

26:19.746 --> 26:22.290
- What are you doing?
- FBI. Out, out, out.

26:23.374 --> 26:26.878
- What the hell are you doing?
- Giving you a little incentive.

26:27.712 --> 26:29.922
Come on. Come on, you son of a--

26:30.298 --> 26:31.924
SLATTERY:
And they found nothing?

26:32.633 --> 26:34.594
Okay, thanks.

26:34.969 --> 26:36.637
Well, your instincts are great, Brad.

26:36.804 --> 26:40.099
But the precinct actually sent a unit over
to Hollander's house today.

26:40.266 --> 26:43.269
An anonymous caller said they saw
an intruder but no one was there.

26:43.436 --> 26:44.979
Damn it.

26:45.146 --> 26:46.981
If you knew about
Bagwell and Hollander...

26:47.148 --> 26:49.317
...why didn't you just head
over there yourself?

26:49.692 --> 26:52.069
Oh, we couldn't find the house.

26:52.820 --> 26:55.490
Really? It's listed.

26:57.033 --> 26:58.493
[KNOCKING]

27:01.829 --> 27:03.331
Excuse me.

27:10.880 --> 27:12.673
Thank you.

27:13.758 --> 27:15.676
Everything okay?

27:16.511 --> 27:19.096
Yeah, yeah, everything's fine.

27:20.807 --> 27:23.976
You ever been to the Fauntleroy Hotel?
It's about 15 minutes from here.

27:24.143 --> 27:27.313
- Never heard of it.
- Well, that's strange.

27:27.480 --> 27:30.066
Because they found this receipt
in Geary's hotel room.

27:30.233 --> 27:31.692
It's from your credit card.

27:35.196 --> 27:36.864
I don't know how that got there.

27:42.620 --> 27:44.914
I think you're being evasive.

27:45.414 --> 27:49.335
- You should tell me the truth, Mr. Bellick.
- What happened to "Brad"?

27:50.628 --> 27:52.922
About seven years ago,
I got my first homicide case.

27:53.089 --> 27:55.091
A woman. Pretty.
She was brutally attacked.

27:55.258 --> 27:57.635
Animal boyfriend left her for dead.

27:57.760 --> 28:00.638
But she was still breathing, barely.

28:00.763 --> 28:03.266
But she punched into her cell phone...

28:03.432 --> 28:06.769
...the killer's number,
so she solved the crime for us.

28:07.562 --> 28:10.106
When we found the receipt, Brad,
it was in Geary's hand...

28:10.273 --> 28:13.442
...his finger pointing to your name.
With his last ounce of strength...

28:13.651 --> 28:15.653
-...he told us you killed him.
- Okay, listen.

28:15.778 --> 28:18.531
Geary and I found Bagwell
in Hollander's house.

28:18.698 --> 28:22.368
We roughed him up until he told us
where he'd hid the 5 million bucks...

28:22.535 --> 28:24.078
...we knew he'd dug up in Utah.

28:24.245 --> 28:26.539
When we found the money,
Geary double-crossed me...

28:26.706 --> 28:28.791
...he hit me in the head
and took the cash.

28:28.958 --> 28:32.253
I had nothing to do with Geary's death.
You hear what I'm saying?

28:32.420 --> 28:34.964
I'm the victim here,
not that son of a bitch.

28:45.099 --> 28:48.352
Oh, come on, come on, come on.

28:48.519 --> 28:49.896
Where you at, baby?

28:55.568 --> 28:57.820
Hey, could you hurry it up?

28:57.987 --> 29:00.907
It's just it's getting really late
and I gotta get home.

29:07.246 --> 29:13.628
And that's 20, 40, 5O and 2O is 70.

29:13.794 --> 29:19.091
One, two, three, four, five is 75.

29:21.093 --> 29:22.929
KACEE:
Excuse me.

29:34.023 --> 29:36.359
You gotta be kidding me.

29:45.618 --> 29:47.244
Ma'am.

29:48.037 --> 29:49.288
KACEE:
Afternoon, officer.

29:50.831 --> 29:53.334
Do you have any ID with you?

29:53.584 --> 29:57.296
No, I walked over here,
so I didn't carry anything with me.

29:57.463 --> 29:59.966
COP:
Did you? Where'd you walk from?

30:00.925 --> 30:02.760
Is there a problem, officer?

30:02.885 --> 30:06.222
There's only a problem
if you make one, Miss Franklin.

30:06.389 --> 30:08.224
You want to tell us
where your husband is?

30:10.935 --> 30:12.770
I don't know.

30:12.895 --> 30:15.940
Place your hands behind your back,
please, ma'am.

30:26.242 --> 30:28.953
Oh, baby, I'm so sorry.

30:44.885 --> 30:47.138
Oh, my God.

30:48.222 --> 30:49.598
Where's Mommy?

30:52.601 --> 30:57.023
Mommy is gonna meet us later, okay?

31:02.737 --> 31:05.531
<i>- Yes?
KIM</i> [OVER <i>PHONE]: Where's the photo?</i>

31:05.823 --> 31:07.241
Bill, there was a tactical error.

31:07.658 --> 31:10.995
I don't want terminology from
the Cover Your Ass Handbook, Paul.

31:11.162 --> 31:14.540
- What happened?
- There were unforeseen circumstances.

31:14.707 --> 31:17.835
- Things that could not be predicted.
- Where's Sara?

31:19.045 --> 31:21.088
She's gone, isn't she?

31:25.676 --> 31:27.636
Yes. She got away.

31:27.845 --> 31:29.847
<i>But there is no way that she--</i>

31:30.973 --> 31:32.683
Bill?

32:05.174 --> 32:07.301
[GRUNTING]

32:44.130 --> 32:46.757
I'm not gonna let you die.

32:50.344 --> 32:51.554
I love you.

32:54.682 --> 32:56.725
You know that, don't you?

33:11.407 --> 33:13.409
MICHAEL:
Too many.

33:14.577 --> 33:18.414
Too many people died
because I wanted you to be free.

33:18.789 --> 33:20.791
You couldn't have known, Michael.

33:21.709 --> 33:24.420
You couldn't have known
it would've ended up like this.

33:24.587 --> 33:25.880
But it did.

33:28.883 --> 33:30.384
They wanted him.

33:31.385 --> 33:33.846
They wanted him in the ground...

33:34.221 --> 33:35.598
...and they got their wish.

33:37.224 --> 33:40.019
This thing's not gonna end here,
Michael.

33:41.896 --> 33:43.981
- I know.
- It's gonna keep spreading.

33:46.567 --> 33:49.278
Their hands are gonna get more
and more bloody.

33:49.987 --> 33:51.572
The question is...

33:51.739 --> 33:55.701
...is the blood on their hands or ours?

34:02.374 --> 34:03.626
I'm sorry, GUYS-

34:05.085 --> 34:06.795
We gotta go.

34:26.023 --> 34:29.443
Get back on with border patrol. Call
the Navy Reserve Air Station in Dallas.

34:29.610 --> 34:30.819
They've got planes on alert.

34:31.027 --> 34:33.614
We need an intercept
of a white single-engine A-36 Beech...

34:33.781 --> 34:35.114
...heading toward the border.

34:35.282 --> 34:38.284
Call Mexico. Get clearance
for an international pursuit.

34:38.452 --> 34:41.538
Tell them if they've gotta take
the plane down, just do it.

35:25.374 --> 35:27.293
SUCRE:
Come on, guys.

35:28.085 --> 35:29.336
Guys, come on.

35:29.545 --> 35:31.005
Come on, guys.

35:33.841 --> 35:35.092
What?

35:37.386 --> 35:38.804
We're staying.

35:40.097 --> 35:41.974
[SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

35:44.643 --> 35:47.980
SUCRE: Michael, this is what
we've been waiting for.

35:48.147 --> 35:50.733
Maybe we'll see you
down there somewhere.

35:51.775 --> 35:54.236
I can't talk you out of this one, can I?

36:01.910 --> 36:03.162
Oh, I hope so.

36:04.246 --> 36:06.040
Be good.

36:06.206 --> 36:09.793
Thank you, Michael.
Thank you for everything.

36:15.299 --> 36:17.134
- You take care of him, all right?
- I will.

36:18.510 --> 36:19.762
<i>Fly safe, pap/-</i>

36:23.932 --> 36:25.768
Give them hell.

36:43.452 --> 36:46.163
- Panama would've been good.
- Are you ready for this?

36:46.622 --> 36:49.166
- Been waiting years.
- Good to hear it.

36:49.291 --> 36:52.169
Because today's the day
we stop running.

37:08.769 --> 37:10.813
- What now?
- We go back to the car...

37:10.979 --> 37:14.024
...drive to a border town,
find a cell phone signal...

37:14.191 --> 37:16.318
...and call Sara.

37:27.996 --> 37:29.998
Where the hell are those jets?

37:38.298 --> 37:40.968
[PLANE APPROACHING]

37:41.135 --> 37:43.470
- You hear that?
- Yeah.

37:47.099 --> 37:48.809
Pull over.

38:00.654 --> 38:03.157
MICHAEL:
They're going after Sucre.

38:03.657 --> 38:05.868
They're gonna take him down.

38:06.243 --> 38:09.288
- How'd they find out?
- I don't know.

38:13.584 --> 38:15.377
Michael.

38:46.116 --> 38:49.328
What the hell is going on? If you could
arrest me you would have already.

38:49.703 --> 38:52.164
- I'm out of here.
- Not really an option for you.

38:52.331 --> 38:55.584
What've you got? A receipt?
He left it in his pocket. A fight? Big deal.

38:55.751 --> 38:59.379
I got 1O pals in Chicago who'll tell you
Geary and I threw down once a month.

38:59.546 --> 39:02.883
You're right. Any of those things
on their own, probably not enough.

39:03.050 --> 39:04.593
But when you add this.

39:05.511 --> 39:07.221
What the hell is that?

39:07.387 --> 39:09.598
You left a message for Mr. Geary.

39:11.099 --> 39:13.435
BELLICK <i>[ON MESSAGE]:
You thieving son of a bitch.</i>

39:13.602 --> 39:16.813
<i>You better get down on your knees
and pray to God that I don't find you.</i>

39:16.980 --> 39:21.568
<i>Because if! do, mark my words,
I'm gonna gut you bow to stern.</i>

39:24.321 --> 39:25.781
You wanna hear it again?

39:28.450 --> 39:29.785
Now, at this juncture, Brad...

39:29.952 --> 39:33.121
...things will go a whole lot easier
for you if you admit to the crime.

39:33.622 --> 39:37.125
Now, you listen to me,
you manipulative little bitch.

39:38.418 --> 39:41.421
I did not kill Roy Geary!
You understand what I'm telling you?

39:41.588 --> 39:44.341
Bagwell set me up!
Get your hands off of me!

39:44.841 --> 39:47.719
You are under arrest for the murder
of Roy William Geary.

39:47.886 --> 39:50.347
You have a right to remain silent.
Anything you say...

39:50.472 --> 39:53.141
...can be used against you.
You have the right to a lawyer...

39:53.350 --> 39:55.978
...and to have him present.
If you cannot hire a lawyer...

39:56.144 --> 39:58.146
...the court will appoint one for you.

40:05.237 --> 40:07.114
[RINGING]

40:08.115 --> 40:09.366
WOMAN [OVER <i>PHONE]:
Pres/dent Reynolds ' ofi/ce.</i>

40:09.491 --> 40:10.826
This is Agent Paul Kellerman.

40:10.993 --> 40:13.495
I need to speak with the president
right now, please.

40:13.662 --> 40:16.748
<i>I'm sorry, this administration
isn't familiar with an Agent Kellerman.</i>

40:16.915 --> 40:21.169
June, it's me.
I need to speak with Carolyn now.

40:21.837 --> 40:23.171
If you don't put me through...

40:23.380 --> 40:26.425
...I'll make certain the president knows
that you did not allow me...

40:26.592 --> 40:29.845
...to provide her with some very
important information. Now.

40:30.762 --> 40:34.683
<i>I'm sorry, this administration
isn't familiar with an Agent--</i>

40:46.528 --> 40:48.614
<i>VOICE:
Please leave a message after the tone.</i>

40:49.698 --> 40:51.700
Bill, don't do this.

40:51.867 --> 40:55.037
<i>KELLERMAN". I've dedicated my life
to this country. To Carolyn.</i>

40:55.203 --> 40:57.039
<i>Everything I have, I give.</i>

40:57.205 --> 41:00.917
Every photo. Every file. Get rid of it all.

41:01.084 --> 41:04.046
- Make <i>him</i> a <i>ghost.
- I've been a perfect sold/er.</i>

41:04.212 --> 41:07.049
<i>I've never asked anything of you ever.</i>

41:07.549 --> 41:09.885
<i>But I'm asking now.</i>

41:10.052 --> 41:12.220
<i>Bill, don't do this.</i>

41:17.517 --> 41:21.730
- I don't see him.
- Trust me, we haven't lost him yet.

41:30.739 --> 41:32.866
Linc, stop the car.

41:33.033 --> 41:35.786
- What?
- We gotta stop the car.

41:42.334 --> 41:44.127
That's a radio tower over there.

41:44.294 --> 41:47.297
It must be picking up
some kind of analog signal.

41:47.464 --> 41:50.300
We gotta get closer. Turn around.

41:51.093 --> 41:54.721
- What about your friend back there?
- If we're gonna go down...

41:54.888 --> 41:56.473
...might as well go down swinging.

42:06.483 --> 42:08.276
All right.

42:08.485 --> 42:10.487
Come OH, come on, come OH.

42:14.741 --> 42:17.661
We are in business. It's going through.

42:18.120 --> 42:19.329
All right.

42:19.496 --> 42:22.082
MICHAEL: Come on, Sara, pick up.
Pick up, pick up, pick up.

42:31.508 --> 42:33.301
[COUGHING]

42:34.636 --> 42:36.722
[GRUNTING]

42:42.769 --> 42:44.229
[RINGING]

42:46.648 --> 42:48.608
Sara.

43:10.714 --> 43:12.382
SARA [OVER PHONE]:
<i>Hello?</i>

43:13.008 --> 43:14.468
<i>Hello, Michael?</i>

43:14.885 --> 43:16.553
<i>Michael?</i>

43:16.970 --> 43:18.722
<i>Michael?</i>

43:57.427 --> 43:59.513
[ENGLISH SDH]
